    &gt; I am having a very annoying problem when I use JUnit. 
    &gt; I have a helper class that loads a properties file. I 
    &gt; wrote a simple class with a main to test calling the 
    &gt; helper class and loading the file, and 
    &gt; the file IS found and loaded without a problem. However, 
    &gt; when I use a JUnit test to call the code that calls the 
    &gt; helper class, the properties 
    &gt; file IS NOT found. But if I put the method to load the 
    &gt; properties file INSIDE the JUnit test class, the file IS 
    &gt; found and loaded. 
    &gt; 
