    &gt; properties file. Both the Windows system classpath and 
    &gt; the IDE&#39;s classpath point to 
    &gt; build/classes and the jar files. I have the same problem 
    &gt; whether I run from a command line or within the IDE.
    &gt;          
    &gt; Here is the method to load the properties (this works 
    &gt; when not using JUnit):
    &gt;      private void loadProperties() {
    &gt; 	    InputStream in = null;
    &gt;                   in = 
    &gt; this.getClass().getResourceAsStream(&quot;/config/aoi.properties&quot;);
    &gt; 			if (in == null) {
    &gt; 				if ( 
    &gt; Logger.getInstance().isDebugEnabled() ) {
    &gt; 				    
    &gt; Logger.getInstance().getCat().fatal(&quot;Unable to load 
    &gt; properties -- using defaults&quot;);
    &gt; 				    remoteRegistryPort = 1099;
